# HomeCareNew Project Context

- Stack: React 19 + Vite + Zustand + Tailwind CSS v4; TypeScript (`.ts` / `.tsx`).
- Entry flow: `index.html` -> `src/main.tsx` -> `src/App.tsx`.
- Navigation is view-state based (no URL router): `currentView` in `src/store/useStore.ts`.
- Main UI domains live in `src/components/{auth,home,services,cart,booking,admin,layout,common}`.
- Global app state is centralized in `src/store/useStore.ts` (auth, admin lock, views, services, bookings, cart, UI overlays, toast).
- Shared domain types live in `src/types/domain.ts`.
- App data comes from local mocks in `src/data/*`; there is no backend/API data layer yet.
- Session and data are in-memory only; browser refresh resets runtime state.

## Rules For Future Changes

- Preserve the current view contract (`home`, `services`, `booking`, `admin`) unless the task explicitly asks for routing redesign.
- Prefer Zustand selectors (`useStore(s => s.x)`) and keep state updates within the existing store model.
- Reuse existing shared primitives before adding new dependencies: `Modal`, `Toast`, `Reveal`, `CartDrawer`, `DetailSheet`.
- Keep visual consistency with Tailwind utility patterns and theme tokens defined in `src/index.css`.
- When editing auth/admin/booking flows, treat current PIN/OTP/login behavior as demo-only and client-side.
- If adding real backend/auth/payment integrations, place them in isolated service modules and preserve mock-friendly behavior unless asked otherwise.
- Match existing code style: semicolon-less TS/TSX, single quotes, functional React components.
- Validate changes with `npm run lint` and `npx tsc --noEmit`; use `npm run dev`/`npm run build` for behavior and build checks.

## Known Non-Production Assumptions

- Security is intentionally weak right now (client-side auth and admin gating).
- Payment behavior is simulated in booking flow.
- `README.md` may be outdated (still close to default Vite template).
